What are the key principles for success in Scala programming? Can you put them in the correct order? Here's a hint - these principles involve proper memory management, consistent and readable code, effective use of libraries and APIs, thorough testing and debugging, and continuous learning and improvement. Can you guess what they are? Use this Scala code to guide you:
val principles = List("Proper memory management", "Consistent and readable code", "Effective use of libraries and APIs", "Thorough testing and debugging", "Continuous learning and improvement")
// Put the principles in the correct order
val orderedPrinciples = principles.reverse
// Print out the ordered principles
println("The key principles for success in Scala programming are:")
for (p <- orderedPrinciples) {
  println(p)
}
Good luck!
